    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix GTP-U instance initialization failure in gtpv1Init()\n\n### Summary\nThe `gtpv1Init()` function in the OAI 5G core was failing to properly initialize GTP-U instances due to an incorrect instance lookup mechanism. The function would return -1 (GTPNOK) even when the UDP socket was successfully created, preventing the GTP-U thread from starting.\n\nThis issue occurred because the function was using a macro designed for retrieving existing instances (`getInstRetInt`) rather than directly accessing the newly created instance. Under normal operation, this caused the CU-UP to fail N3 interface initialization, resulting in PDU session establishment failures.\n\nThe problem was most noticeable when running CU-UP in standalone mode where GTP-U initialization is critical for user plane functionality.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/ocp-gtpu/gtp_itf.cpp`: Replaced incorrect instance lookup with direct access in `gtpv1Init()` function\n"
}